    <string name="explanation_runtime_title">Runtime</string>
    <string name="explanation_runtime_body">This section controls whether the local Ghosthand runtime is active. It controls the foreground service and the local API availability for OpenClaw. It may need foreground-service permission and the normal Android runtime environment to start correctly. Ghosthand and OpenClaw can use the runtime only when it is active.</string>
    <string name="explanation_permissions_title">Permissions</string>
    <string name="explanation_permissions_body">This section governs sensitive capabilities such as Accessibility and Screenshot capture. It controls the relationship between system authorization, Ghosthand policy, and effective usability. It may require manual Android authorization flows before a capability is usable. Ghosthand and OpenClaw may use a capability only when system authorization and Ghosthand policy both allow it.</string>
    <string name="explanation_accessibility_title">Accessibility Control</string>
    <string name="explanation_accessibility_body">Accessibility control lets Ghosthand read UI structure and perform semantic actions such as tap, swipe, and global navigation. It controls the accessibility-backed action path used by OpenClaw. It requires the Ghosthand accessibility service to be enabled and connected in Android settings. Ghosthand and OpenClaw may use it only when Android authorization and Ghosthand policy both allow it.</string>
    <string name="explanation_screenshot_title">Screenshot Capture</string>
    <string name="explanation_screenshot_body">Screenshot capture gives Ghosthand a visual snapshot of the current screen. It controls the image-capture path used by OpenClaw when a screenshot route is requested. It may require MediaProjection consent or accessibility screenshot readiness depending on the device path that is actually available. Ghosthand and OpenClaw may use it only when system authorization and Ghosthand policy both allow it.</string>
    <string name="explanation_diagnostics_title">Diagnostics</string>
    <string name="explanation_diagnostics_body">Diagnostics exposes secondary runtime truth such as build identity, current foreground package, and helper status. It controls observability rather than primary execution flow. It may surface information that depends on current runtime state and Android permissions already granted elsewhere. Ghosthand and OpenClaw do not gain new execution power here; this section helps a human inspect the current system state.</string>
